  "text": "yet it cannot distinguish between monomials of the same degree such as xy 2 and z 3 . However, Gröbner basis are computed over finite sets of monomials rather than over all monomials with exponents in Z k ≥0 . This last fact together with a careful selection of the ordering vector are at the core of the efficient Universal Gröbner bases algorithms [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
